  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Dragon fruit growers: moving from an association to a cooperative model</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Uong Bi Dragon Fruit Association has 60 members. The association covers 5 communes in the district Uong Bi. Total area under production is 50 ha. Total production is of 500 MT (max is 35 - 50 MT/ha). In 2016 a volume is expected of 600 MT with an average price of around 30.000 VND/kg. The association has no selling plan.

Expected to attract members from other districts. Total 120 ha dragon fruit in Quang Ninh. In Uong Bi district expansion is expected of 50 ha in the coming 5 years.The association is at this moment not an appropriate legal entity for collective marketing, neither for internal capitalization. A cooperative structure is needed in future to raise share capital (as is being done in the early lychee cooperative in Uong Bi). The organisation follows the legal requirements for associations. The board has capacity but needs more business and governance skills to make the transformation.

Proposal 2016: 

1. Visit a successfully (transformed) cooperative to learn transfomation process from association2. Promotion for better market price; product promotion and marketing 3. Training in marketing skills (already done)4. Increase knowledge about cooperatives (already done) and disseminate knowledge.5. Participate in development of a model for the association as service provider for coops.6. Participate in value chain analysis in Dragon Fruit in Quang Ninh Province.

Increase awareness of knowledge on cooperative model, marketing and value chain</narrative>
  </description>
